-- testregex.sql -- exercise pg_tre's regex engine with the AT&T regex(3)
-- conformance corpus (github/codeberg gregburd/testregex, the classic
-- Glenn Fowler / AT&T Research test suite).
--
-- This test is GENERATED by scripts/gen-testregex.py from the *.dat files
-- in that repository.  Do not edit by hand; re-run the generator to refresh.
--
-- Construction:
--   * Only ERE-flagged ('E'/'BE') rows are used (TRE compiles with
--     REG_EXTENDED).  Backreference / collating-element / word-boundary
--     rows and rows whose expectation diverges from a reference ERE engine
--     are dropped, so every embedded case has a known, engine-agnostic
--     verdict.
--   * EXACT bucket (k=0): tre_amatch(input, regex, 0) must equal the
--     corpus verdict (a position tuple => match; NOMATCH => no match).
--   * APPROX bucket (>=50% of all cases): the input of a matching row is
--     mutated by d in {1,2} random edits (insert / delete / substitute --
--     the "approximate distance phrases"), then tre_amatch(mutated, regex,
--     k) with k>=d must still match.  Anchored (^/$) patterns are excluded
--     from this bucket; they remain in the exact bucket.  Mutations come
--     from a fixed-seed RNG so this file is fully deterministic.
--
